] Once a plaintiff has satisfied the injury requirement under Section 17203 of the UCL, "[s]uch injuries satisfy the plain meaning of section 17204's 'lost money or property' requirement, qualify as injury in fact, and would permit a plaintiff to seek an 
injunction against the offending business practice even in the absence of any basis for restitution." Kwikset, 246 P.3d at 895.

